responses.body:
{
  "id": "",
  "kind": "dns#project",
  "number": "",
  "quota": {
    "dnsKeysPerManagedZone": {{faker 'number.int' max=99999}},
    "gkeClustersPerManagedZone": {{faker 'number.int' max=99999}},
    "gkeClustersPerPolicy": {{faker 'number.int' max=99999}},
    "gkeClustersPerResponsePolicy": {{faker 'number.int' max=99999}},
    "itemsPerRoutingPolicy": {{faker 'number.int' max=99999}},
    "kind": "dns#quota",
    "managedZones": {{faker 'number.int' max=99999}},
    "managedZonesPerGkeCluster": {{faker 'number.int' max=99999}},
    "managedZonesPerNetwork": {{faker 'number.int' max=99999}},
    "networksPerManagedZone": {{faker 'number.int' max=99999}},
    "networksPerPolicy": {{faker 'number.int' max=99999}},
    "networksPerResponsePolicy": {{faker 'number.int' max=99999}},
    "peeringZonesPerTargetNetwork": {{faker 'number.int' max=99999}},
    "policies": {{faker 'number.int' max=99999}},
    "resourceRecordsPerRrset": {{faker 'number.int' max=99999}},
    "responsePolicies": {{faker 'number.int' max=99999}},
    "responsePolicyRulesPerResponsePolicy": {{faker 'number.int' max=99999}},
    "rrsetAdditionsPerChange": {{faker 'number.int' max=99999}},
    "rrsetDeletionsPerChange": {{faker 'number.int' max=99999}},
    "rrsetsPerManagedZone": {{faker 'number.int' max=99999}},
    "targetNameServersPerManagedZone": {{faker 'number.int' max=99999}},
    "targetNameServersPerPolicy": {{faker 'number.int' max=99999}},
    "totalRrdataSizePerChange": {{faker 'number.int' max=99999}},
    "whitelistedKeySpecs": [
      {
        "algorithm": "{{oneOf (array 'RSASHA1' 'RSASHA256' 'RSASHA512' 'ECDSAP256SHA256' 'ECDSAP384SHA384')}}",
        "keyLength": {{faker 'number.int' max=99999}},
        "keyType": "{{oneOf (array 'KEY_SIGNING' 'ZONE_SIGNING')}}",
        "kind": "dns#dnsKeySpec"
      }
    ]
  }
}

Gets the access control policy for a resource. Returns an empty policy if the resource exists and does not have a policy set.
Sets the access control policy on the specified resource. Replaces any existing policy. Can return `NOT_FOUND`, `INVALID_ARGUMENT`, and `PERMISSION_DENIED` errors.

Returns permissions that a caller has on the specified resource. If the resource does not exist, this returns an empty set of permissions, not a `NOT_FOUND` error. Note: This operation is designed to be used for building permission-aware UIs and command-line tools, not for authorization checking. This operation may "fail open" without warning.
